# Privacy Policy update workflow

Whenever you change the Money Diary Privacy Policy, update **all** of the following in the same change:

## 1. Last updated date

Set `PRIVACY_POLICY_LAST_UPDATED` in `src/features/legal/content/privacy-policy.ts` to the change date (human-readable, e.g. `June 22, 2026`). This drives the date shown at the top of `/privacy`.

## 2. Policy update history (required)

Prepend a new entry to `privacyPolicyUpdateLog` in the same file:

```typescript
{
  date: 'June 22, 2026', // must match PRIVACY_POLICY_LAST_UPDATED when this is the latest change
  summary: 'Short title of why the policy changed',
  changes: [
    'What was added or changed — be specific',
    'Another bullet if needed',
  ],
}
```

- Newest entry **first** (reverse chronological).
- Bullets describe what was **added, removed, or clarified** — not internal refactors.
- Do not skip the log when only “small” wording changes; users should see what changed and when.

## 3. Policy body sections

Edit `privacyPolicySections` so the legal text matches the product. Do not leave contradictions between sections and the update log.

## 4. Rendering

`PrivacyPolicyContent` already renders `privacyPolicyUpdateLog`. Do not remove that section. If you extend the data shape, update the component in the same PR.

## Checklist before finishing

- [ ] `PRIVACY_POLICY_LAST_UPDATED` updated
- [ ] New `privacyPolicyUpdateLog` entry with matching date
- [ ] Relevant `privacyPolicySections` updated
- [ ] `/privacy` still shows last updated + update history
